description:
&lt;p&gt;East Lancashire Hospitals NHS Trust is a busy Trust covering a population of around 550,000, and comprises of two main hospital sites – one based at the Royal Blackburn Teaching Hospital which mainly deals with non-elective cases, and the other at Burnley General Teaching Hospital which deals with elective cases. There are three smaller sites at Pendle, Accrington and Rossendale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Locum Consultant Physician with an Interest in Respiratory Medicine. We would particularly welcome applicants with a special interest in COPD, asthma or interstitial lung disease although other subspecialty interests will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be based primarily at Royal Blackburn Teaching Hospital. The post involves out-patient and in-patient duties and a regular commitment to on call for general medicine The post also provides opportunities to develop other areas of special interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a team of 7.5 respiratory physicians. Existing colleagues have special interests in TB, pleural disease, lung cancer, cough, sleep disordered breathing, interstitial lung disease, COPD, asthma and NIV. There is a large respiratory specialist nurse team focusing on COPD and asthma patients who work across the trust and in the community. In addition, there are four lung cancer specialist nurses, 3 TB specialist nurses, 2 Respiratory Advanced Nurse Practitioners and a respiratory physiology team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants must have full registration with the GMC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would be coming to join a committed and experienced team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr S Khalid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consultant and Clinical Director&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;saifudin.khalid@elht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01254 733638&lt;/p&gt;
